



Sir
Sunday Morng [1769]



I will take particular Care of the Paper you have sent me, & I am of Opinion I may safely promise you that the Appointment to the Surveyorship mentiond will not be made out before the Time you speak ofI assure you I cannot help considering this as for a particular matter, wherein some forms may be dispensd with under proper Care that the College receives no Detriment, & if this shoud be so, it will be a pleasure to me to
[283]
have this done as far as I am able in the most full manner agreeable to Your Wishes.1 Have the Honor to be Sir Your very hble Servt

J. Horrocks

